                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 14.043,
                                "byte_start": 89849,
                                "byte_stop": 146065,
                                "text": "Justice Souter has our opinion this morning in 06-84, Safeco Insurance Company versus Burr, and the consolidated case 06-100, GEICO General Insurance versus Edo."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 14.043,
                        "stop": 350.015,
                        "byte_start": 146065,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15042,
                            "name": "David H. Souter",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/david_h_souter",
                            "last_name": "Souter",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2686,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 655362000,
                                    "date_end": 1246251600,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 14.043,
                                "stop": 19.677,
                                "byte_start": 146065,
                                "byte_stop": 168634,
                                "text": "These cases come to us on a writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.677,
                                "stop": 36.723,
                                "byte_start": 168634,
                                "byte_stop": 236762,
                                "text": "The Fair Credit Reporting Act required notice to any consumer who suffers from what the act calls \u201cadverse action\u201d based in whole or in part on any information in the consumer report which includes, credit reports and credit scores."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 36.723,
                                "stop": 44.354,
                                "byte_start": 236762,
                                "byte_stop": 267273,
                                "text": "This notice tells the consumer about the adverse action and gives details about how to dispute the accuracy of the report used."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 44.354,
                                "stop": 54.466,
                                "byte_start": 267273,
                                "byte_stop": 307815,
                                "text": "For purposes of this case, the act defines an \u201cadverse action\u201d as \u201can increase in any charge for any insurance existing or applied for.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.466,
                                "stop": 66.816,
                                "byte_start": 307815,
                                "byte_stop": 357134,
                                "text": "Under the act \u201cconsumers can sue businesses that fail to comply and if the business\u2019 violation is willful the effected the consumer is entitled to actual statutory and punitive damages.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.816,
                                "stop": 77.093,
                                "byte_start": 357134,
                                "byte_stop": 398303,
                                "text": "GEICO the petitioner in number 06-100 took respondent Edo\u2019s credit score into account when it issued him a new insurance policy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 77.093,
                                "stop": 88.748,
                                "byte_start": 398303,
                                "byte_stop": 444905,
                                "text": "Since the rate that Edo received was the same he would have gotten if GEICO had not looked at his credit score at all, the GEICO did not send him an \u201cadverse action\u201d notice."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.748,
                                "stop": 98.695,
                                "byte_start": 444905,
                                "byte_stop": 484716,
                                "text": "Edo sued GEICO alleging that it had willfully violated the act\u2019s notice requirement but the district court granted summary judgment to GEICO."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 98.695,
                                "stop": 111.387,
                                "byte_start": 484716,
                                "byte_stop": 535498,
                                "text": "Safeco the petitioner in 06-84 also took credit information into account when it issued new insurance policies to respondents Charles Burr, and Shannon Massey."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.387,
                                "stop": 118.415,
                                "byte_start": 535498,
                                "byte_stop": 563606,
                                "text": "Since Safeco did not think that the notice requirement applied to initial rates of a new insurance it did not give them notice."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.415,
                                "stop": 125.26,
                                "byte_start": 563606,
                                "byte_stop": 590982,
                                "text": "Burr and Massey joined a proposed class action against Safeco alleging willful violation of the act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 125.26,
                                "stop": 128.986,
                                "byte_start": 590982,
                                "byte_stop": 605820,
                                "text": "The District Court granted summary judgment for Safeco."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.986,
                                "stop": 132.879,
                                "byte_start": 605820,
                                "byte_stop": 621389,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit reversed in both cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 132.879,
                                "stop": 146.397,
                                "byte_start": 621389,
                                "byte_stop": 675514,
                                "text": "It held that an \u201cadverse action\u201d occurs whenever a consumer would have gotten a lower rate if his credit score had been more favorable and that the notice requirement applies to initial charges for new insurance policies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.397,
                                "stop": 161.195,
                                "byte_start": 675514,
                                "byte_stop": 734656,
                                "text": "It also held that an insurer willfully fails to comply with the act if it acts with \u201creckless disregard\u201d of the act\u2019s requirements and the Court of Appeals remanded both cases for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 161.195,
                                "stop": 167.288,
                                "byte_start": 734656,
                                "byte_stop": 759002,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the clerk today we reverse the judgments in both cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.288,
                                "stop": 176.831,
                                "byte_start": 759002,
                                "byte_stop": 797245,
                                "text": "Where willfulness is a statutory condition of civil liability, we have taken it to cover not only knowing violations of a standard, but reckless ones as well."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.831,
                                "stop": 180.286,
                                "byte_start": 797245,
                                "byte_stop": 811038,
                                "text": "This construction is consistent with common law usage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.286,
                                "stop": 191.319,
                                "byte_start": 811038,
                                "byte_stop": 855132,
                                "text": "Since congress was presumably aware of the background and didn\u2019t point in a different direction we agree with the Ninth Circuit the willful failure covers reckless violations of the act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 191.319,
                                "stop": 207.023,
                                "byte_start": 855132,
                                "byte_stop": 918035,
                                "text": "We also agree that an initial rate charged for new insurance can be an increase in an insurance charge as the act uses that term in \u201cadverse action\u201d requiring notice."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 207.023,
                                "stop": 218.255,
                                "byte_start": 918035,
                                "byte_stop": 962966,
                                "text": "This reading fits with the act\u2019s broad statement of purpose and it is unlikely that congress meant to distinguish newly insured from renewal applicants in this context."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 218.255,
                                "stop": 224.451,
                                "byte_start": 962966,
                                "byte_stop": 987730,
                                "text": "Notice is not required however unless the credit report is a necessary condition of the increase."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 224.451,
                                "stop": 237.825,
                                "byte_start": 987730,
                                "byte_stop": 1041229,
                                "text": "This is the most natural reading of the act\u2019s based on language and congress probably meant to prompt consumer challenges only when the consumer would gain something, if the challenge succeeded."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 237.825,
                                "stop": 264.822,
                                "byte_start": 1041229,
                                "byte_stop": 1149167,
                                "text": "This conclusion leads us to hold that the comparative baseline for determining whether an initial rate is a disadvantageous increase, is what the applicant would have gotten, if his credit report had not been considered, this we think best reflects the concern for practical consequences that congress showed in adopting the causation requirement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 264.822,
                                "stop": 270.13,
                                "byte_start": 1149167,
                                "byte_stop": 1170378,
                                "text": "Therefore, Edo was not entitled to notice and GEICO didn\u2019t violate the act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 270.13,
                                "stop": 277.47,
                                "byte_start": 1170378,
                                "byte_stop": 1199740,
                                "text": "Safeco on the other hand may have violated the act but we find that if it did it did not act recklessly."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 277.47,
                                "stop": 289.974,
                                "byte_start": 1199740,
                                "byte_stop": 1249790,
                                "text": "The common law regards \u201crecklessness\u201d as conduct entailing an objectively high risk of harm, which here would be a risk of course of violating the act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 289.974,
                                "stop": 300.871,
                                "byte_start": 1249790,
                                "byte_stop": 1293362,
                                "text": "Safeco did not have the benefit of guidance from the Courts of Appeals or the Federal Trade Commission and his reading of the act had a reasonable foundation in the statutory text."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 300.871,
                                "stop": 312.022,
                                "byte_start": 1293362,
                                "byte_stop": 1337980,
                                "text": "Since we cannot say that Safeco\u2019s reading was even objectively unreasonable it falls well short of raising the high risk of violating the act necessary for reckless liability."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 312.022,
                                "stop": 324.098,
                                "byte_start": 1337980,
                                "byte_stop": 1386254,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia joins the opinion as to all but footnotes 11 and 15 and some of you can guess what is in footnotes 11 and 15."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 324.098,
                                "stop": 337.552,
                                "byte_start": 1386254,
                                "byte_stop": 1440066,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas and Justice Alito join as to all but part III-A and Justice Stevens and Justice Ginsburg joined parts I, II, III-A and IV-B."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 337.552,
                                "stop": 350.015,
                                "byte_start": 1440066,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed an opinion concurring in part and in the judgment in which Justice Ginsburg joins and Justice Thomas has filed an opinion concurring in part in which Justice Alito joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
